    "department": "Client Service",
    "description": "Who We Are:\n\nSequoia is the strategic partner helping investor-backed companies of all sizes achieve their business goals through smarter people spend. For 24 years, we’ve guided the most innovative employers to navigate growth and get the most out of their global people investment. With our expert advisory team and integrated platform, we help clients drive business impact through their total comp and benefits, improving executive decision making, controlling costs, protecting the business, and elevating the employee experience. Visit Sequoia.com http://Sequoia.com or follow us on LinkedIn https://www.linkedin.com/company/sequoia-tpi/%22%20/t%20%22_blank to learn more.\n\nThis position is located in Tempe, AZ.\n\nFast growing companies require solutions to assist with expansion, the Client Solutions Specialist (CSS) plays a critical role in leading the client experience by implementing system solutions to address each client’s individual needs.\n\nThe CSS will be responsible for implementing systems that address needs such as Time and Attendance, PTO Request Module, and others, ensuring this process is smooth and successful. Additionally, the CSS will project manage while collaborating with the Client Experience Manager (CXM), Human Resource Business Partner (HRBP), and Payroll to ensure the client’s integrations are implemented timely (initially) and are accurately maintained (on-going).\n\nOnce implementation has concluded, the CSS serves as the primary point of knowledge and triages any questions from the CXM, HRBP, Payroll team. Finally, the CSS will lead ongoing internal/external trainings and maintain/update the knowledge base. This position requires strong project management skills, passion for client service, and excellent communication and relationship skills. The individual should embody and promote our culture in daily relationships with clients and our teams.\n\n - Meet with client contacts (C-Suite, VPs, Executive, Head of People, Etc.) to demo system solutions, answer questions, and create an implementation timeline that includes expectations, data requirements, training schedules, etc.\n\n - Partner closely with Client Experience Managers, Onboarding Success Managers, Systems, Payroll, and HRBPs for successful implementation of Time and Attendance, PTO and other solutions for current and implementing clients.\n\n - Facilitates external client system trainings for employees, managers and administrators.\n\n - Point of contact for team education for ongoing system maintenance and facilitates internal trainings.\n\n - Creates and maintains resource materials, SOPs, Knowledge Articles.\n\n - Execute renewals and maintain system operations in Sequoia’s preferred Benefits Administration systems\n\nSequoia’s Culture – Our most important asset \n\n - Integrity \n\n - Passion for service \n\n - Innovative \n\n - Growth oriented \n\n - Caring for others \n\n - Promise-centric \n\n - Focused on relationship building \n\nSequoia provides equal opportunity to all applicants without regard to race, color, creed, religion, citizenship, national origin, age, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, pregnancy, marital status, military or veteran status, disability, or any other basis prohibited by applicable law.\n\nCompensation \u0026 Benefits\nSequoia provides competitive compensation including base salary, performance-based bonus programs, and comprehensive benefits package.\n\nSequoia’s Candidate Privacy Policy \n\nhttps://www.sequoia.com/legal/candidate-privacy-policy/ ",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
